    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-27T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-27T05:00:00-05:00" n="240"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d240">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 P. W./316: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-27T19:00:00+09:00"
                            >July 27, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 27—2:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1103. My 1101, July 27, 3 p.m.,<note n="59" xml:id="d240fn59">Not printed, but
                        see memorandum by the Ambassador in Japan, July 27, 1941, <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v02#pg_534">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 534</ref>.</note> paragraph numbered 3.
                    It seems to me incredible that Admiral Nomura did not promptly telegraph to his
                    Government the President’s proposal presented to the Ambassador 3 days ago.<note
                        n="60" xml:id="d240fn60">See memorandum by the Acting Secretary of State,
                        July 24, 1941, <ref target="frus1931-41v02#pg_527">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 527</ref>.</note> I am convinced of the
                    honesty of Admiral Toyoda’s statement to me this morning that he had not yet
                    received the proposal. The suggestion is unavoidable that extremist elements in
                    the Foreign Office may have withheld the President’s proposal from the Foreign
                    Minister. Might it not be worth while to check up on this with Admiral
                    Nomura?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
